Phase 1 — Ideation & Foundation (Weeks 1–2)
March 4 – March 20
Theme: "Ideate & Know Your Delivery Worker"
Week 1 Tasks

 Finalize persona: Food Delivery (Zomato / Swiggy), Chennai
 Define all 5 parametric trigger conditions and thresholds
 Design weekly premium formula with tiers
 Design 3-layer fraud detection architecture
 Create system architecture and data flow diagram
 Define database schema (workers, policies, claims, trigger_events)
 Initialize GitHub repository with docs folder structure
 Write all 14 documentation files

Week 2 Tasks

 Scaffold React + Vite frontend project
 Scaffold Express.js backend with Sequelize models
 Connect OpenWeatherMap API — live test and verify response format
 Connect OpenAQ API — live test
 Build basic worker onboarding UI prototype (non-functional wireframe)
 Set up Docker Compose (PostgreSQL + Redis + Node + React)
 Record 2-minute Phase 1 strategy video
 Submit Phase 1 deliverables

Phase 1 Deliverable: This README + docs + 2-min video link

Phase 2 — Automation & Protection (Weeks 3–4)
March 21 – April 4
Theme: "Protect Your Worker"
Week 3 Tasks

 Complete worker registration flow (phone OTP → profile → UPI setup)
 Build policy creation UI with tier selection and premium display
 Implement XGBoost risk scoring model (Python FastAPI)
 Build dynamic premium calculator API endpoint
 Set up Bull + Redis background job for 15-min trigger polling
 Implement T-01 (Rain) and T-04 (AQI) triggers end-to-end
 Build basic claim record creation on trigger fire

Week 4 Tasks

 Implement T-02 (Flood), T-03 (Heat), T-05 (Social) triggers
 Build Fraud Layer 1 (GPS validation) and Layer 2 (activity validation)
 Integrate Razorpay sandbox for mock payout processing
 Build worker dashboard: active policy, claim history, earnings protected
 Implement FCM push notifications for claim status
 Integration test: Rain trigger → fraud check → payout → notification
 Record 2-minute Phase 2 demo video

Phase 2 Deliverable: Executable source code + 2-min demo video

Phase 3 — Scale & Optimise (Weeks 5–6)
April 5 – April 17
Theme: "Perfect for Your Worker"
Week 5 Tasks

 Implement Fraud Layer 3 (Isolation Forest ML — statistical anomaly)
 Add GPS spoofing detection (velocity + mock location app detection)
 Build insurer admin dashboard: loss ratios, zone heatmap (Leaflet)
 Integrate Prophet forecasting model for predictive disruption view
 Add forecast-based dynamic pricing on weekly renewal
 Build human review queue UI for 0.7–0.9 fraud score claims
 Implement No-Claim Bonus discount logic

Week 6 Tasks

 Build disruption simulation tool for demo ("trigger fake rainstorm" API)
 End-to-end flow test (simulate → trigger → fraud → approve → payout)
 Final mobile responsiveness and UI polish
 Performance testing (API response times, ML inference latency)
 Prepare final pitch deck PDF
 Record 5-minute final walkthrough demo video
 Submit final package

Phase 3 Deliverable: 5-min demo video + Final Pitch Deck (PDF) + complete codebase

